{"badges":["TM5","TM6"],"preparations":[{"title":"Oyster Emulsion","content":["Shuck oysters, reserving any juices and place in mixing bowl. Pass juice through a muslin cloth then set aside in a separate bowl.","Add breadcrumbs and parsley to mixing bowl then mix <nobr>1 min\/speed 4<\/nobr>. Scrape down sides and base of mixing bowl with spatula.","Place a jug on mixing bowl lid then weigh in 300 g rapeseed oil. Remove jug. Set to <nobr>speed 4<\/nobr> and drizzle rapeseed oil onto mixing bowl lid so that it drips slowly onto blades.","Add filtered oyster juice.","Place a jug on mixing bowl lid then weigh in remaining 300 g rapeseed oil. Remove jug. Set to <nobr>speed 4<\/nobr> and drizzle remaining rapeseed oil onto mixing bowl lid so that it drips slowly onto blades.","Add salt, pepper and lemon juice to taste. Stir then pass mixture through a fine sieve then transfer to a squeezy bottle and keep in fridge until required."]},{"title":"Garnish","content":["Cut cucumber in 3 mm dice. Sprinkle with a little salt then place in a sieve over a bowl to draw a little water out.","Rinse under cold water then drain well. Scatter on a paper towel to dry.","When dry, place dice on an oiled tray in freezer for 3-4 hours until needed."]},{"title":"Squid Crackers","content":["Preheat oven to 65°C. Line 2 large baking trays with silicone mats.","Place rice and stock in mixing bowl then cook <nobr>35-45 min\/95°C\/speed <\/nobr> until rice is very soft.","Add squid ink and cook <nobr>3 min\/70°C\/speed <\/nobr>.","Allow bowl to cool to 60°C then pulse <nobr>Turbo\/1 sec\/2-3 times<\/nobr> to break rice down.","Add lemon juice and fish sauce then pulse <nobr>Turbo\/2 sec\/1 time<\/nobr>. Tip onto prepared trays and spread out to a depth of 2 mm. Dry in oven for 2 hours (65°C). Turn mixture over then dry for a further 1 hour (65°C). Remove from oven and break into pieces (3 cm x 4 cm).","Heat oil in a large saucepan to 190°C.","Drop squid wafers into hot oil (in batches) and cook for 20-30 seconds until puffed. Drain on paper towels. Lightly season then store in an airtight container until needed.","To serve, dot wafers with oyster emulsion, arrange a few pieces of frozen cucumber on each, along with borage leaves. Sprinkle with vinegar powder then serve."]}],"ingredients":[{"title":"Oyster Emulsion","content":["400 g fresh oysters (weight including shells)","110 g breadcrumbs","50 g fresh flat-leaf parsley, leaves only","600 g rapeseed oil","fine sea salt, to taste","lemon juice, to taste","ground black pepper, to taste"]},{"title":"Garnish","content":["½ cucumber, peeled, deseeded","fine sea salt, for sprinkling"]},{"title":"Squid Crackers","content":["325 g long grain rice","650 g fish stock, hot","5 g squid ink, liquid","lemon juice, to taste","5 g fish sauce","rapeseed oil, for frying","fine sea salt, to taste","ground black pepper, to taste","borage leaves, small, cut in half lengthways, for garnish","vinegar powder, for garnish"]}],"id":"r178683","imageLink":"https:\/\/3.bp.blogspot.com\/-SFpO5QCf4Mk\/XZaflTV9UeI\/AAAAAAAAgv4\/yFYe8U8E_KAV_BazX4OaP1a4vWmxbPQwgCLcBGAsYHQ\/s1600\/0_rcU0DhimChuOf03n.png","title":"Squid Crackers, Oyster Emulsion, Frozen Cucumber","publishedAt":"2017-10-09T00:00:00Z","nutrition":{"protein":"44 g","fat":"619 g","uom":"per 1 Total recipe","carbohydrates":"194 g","calories":"27046 kJ \/ 6547 kcal"},"usefulItems":"muslin cloth, jug, fine mesh sieve, squeezy bottle, paper towels, baking trays, silicone baking mats, large saucepan, airtight container, slotted spoon, oyster knife, thermometer, refrigerator, freezer, oven, hob","basicInfo":["advanced","1h 50m","5h 30m","1"]}